==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inchworm
<hw>Inch"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The larva of any geometrid moth. It progresses forward by first
bringing the rear end of the body forward, forming a loop, then moving
the front part of the body; called also <altname>measuring</altname>
worm, <altname>measuringworm</altname>, <altname>spanner</altname>, and
<altname>looper</altname>. See <er>Geometrid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incicurable</ent>⟦br⟧
